row.entry:
Password entered during cluster creation in the CMC utility. If you have chosen to encrypt this password, enter the value in this format: hplefthand_password: {{ '<encrypted vsa-cluster-password>' | hos_user_password_decrypt }}
See for more details.
The hos_user_password_decrypt filter is applied to strings in cinder.conf.j2, even if the line is commented out. So if you run a playbook on a cinder.conf.j2 file that has a commented out encrypted password, and if the key in HOS_USER_PASSWORD_ENCRYPT_KEY is not the one used to encrypt the password, then the decryption will fail and the ansible play will fail. Therefore you should not comment out any lines containing the hos_user_password_decrypt filter, delete them instead.
